<Author>QueenJBelgium
<Content>Simple and Inexpensive We originally booked a hotel online, only to arrive and find it was NOT what we had hoped for and at 11 PM started looking for a different hotel. Lucky for us, we found the Moderno. The wonderful older desk clerk was kindness itself, and gave us an unbelievable rate -69Euro per room, per night including breakfast! We had an interior room-no view but oh so quiet! The room was simple and modern, good sized and immaculate, as was the bathroom. The breakfast was a nice Catalan style with meats, cheeses, cereal, fresh fruit, juice and of course breads, rolls and coffee. Just steps from the Ramblas, it was the perfect small hotel. Not a lot of trimmings, but a good value. ONE note of caution - the rooms are Not soundproof, and you can hear a bit of noise from the other travelers as they come and go. But for that rate I can pack ear plugs! I would gladly return. 
