<Author>Magnum
<Content>Basic as it comes Having never been to Barcelona before I really wanted this short 4 day trip to be unspoiled.However the moderno hotel put an end to that idea. Let me start with its relatively good point. Location is superb. And that鈥檚 it! Right in the heart of the busy Ramblas area you can explore many of Barcelona鈥檚 attractions on foot, as long as you wear a good pair of walking shoes.However the rooms we were allocated were no more than shoeboxes. My friend鈥檚 room was more suitable for a hamster, and his morning view was the inner walls of the hotel itself. More akin to a cheap hostel size or a prison .The bathroom floors were so dirty I had to ask the cleaners to mop it again to remove the hairs all over the floor. The breakfast, although continental is far from adoqute.I was offered more choice in a cheaper hostel in Amsterdam recently. If you鈥檙e a vegetarian then forget it. Its cornflakes or cheese and bread. Once, there was no milk left for coffee, and another morning my half eaten breakfast was swiftly removed from my table as I stood up to get another drink. But by far the worst aspect of this hotel is the noise. I didn鈥檛 get a single good nights sleep whilst there. You hear every footstep and every banging door throughout the night and early next morning. I wish someone on trip advisor had warned readers of this, and I for one would definitely not have stayed. On my last morning they were actually doing work on the next room. The noise was atrocious. And to the end this inaccurately 3starred hotel overcharged for the rooms. I disputed the bill twice pointing out that by email I was assured this was the final amount. This fell on deaf ears and I was advised this is the tax on top. So why tell me otherwise before arrival? All in all, the place is overpriced for what you get, and the service is mediocre at best. The rooms are nothing more than tiny cupboards and the food as bare as it can comes. If you鈥檙e stuck, and there is nowhere else to choose, then maybe worth a look. But confirm in writing the total Inc tax before hand, and ask about the view of the room first. Also, be sure to take ear plugs, you鈥檒l need them. 
